{"has_more_entries": true, "subscriptions": "", "error": "", "posts": [{"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2027421601248006446", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASG0C1wdV", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 163, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8453221, "raw_content": "", "author": "RYTHMICRIOT", "created": 1772267453632, "profile_picture": "unkHmy325PwW", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Smurfection", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASG0C1wdV.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/i/status/2027421601248006446", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Fuck John Thune...", "last_comment_created": 1772293426976, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 3, "score_up": 163, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 0, "created": 1475945461000, "id": "784798261781598208", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1852055748832092160/jAG_GCHV_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Leader John Thune", "username": "LeaderJohnThune"}, "content": "Donald Trump should withdraw and Mike Pence should be our nominee effective immediately.", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 9190}, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 66, "created": 1772209952000, "id": "2027421601248006446", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2024847791181209600/215vbVVO_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Grokius Maximus \u2694\ufe0f", "username": "alx"}, "content": "There were signs", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 8824}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASG0DAcLB", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 32, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8454349, "raw_content": "After this initial success, because America is very good at dropping bombs, but not at \"after\" part, there will be a political price to pay at home.\n\nThere always is. \n\nPolls may reflect an immediate positive result for Trump, mostly because US lives were not lost, and the operation is considered to be successful.  \n\nBut that will change.   Voters in the next few months will not be looking at these actions against Iran as any motivation to vote for Republicans. Not when the SAVE ACT can't be passed, election integrity not solved, and zero arrests for all the assaults on the right, and those involved with Epstein. \n\nOnly a tiny fraction of the base support striking Iran, but they are the loudest.  In fact, if anything, the coalition of voters that Trump assembled to win 2024, from across a wide spectrum, libertarians, cross over Dems etc, will be more divided because of these actions if they do not get wins here at home for American's that are of equal scale or more so, than our giant flexing of military muscle abroad for Israel.\n\nWhat comes next for Iran, Trump is leaving to the Iranian's, and that is even more complex a situation than we had to deal with in Iraq.  \n\nYou can have your strikes on Iran. But you cannot have no strikes on the deep state, and a Republican congress that cannot codify anything to benefit Americans, and say you are winning anything at this point.\n\nMaybe i'm wrong, but history proves how these things play out. ", "author": "MemphisMontoya71", "created": 1772299178788, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Cakes4077", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "This Iran mess, yes it is a mess, regime change is never not messy.  ", "last_comment_created": 1772304885107, "content": "<p>After this initial success, because America is very good at dropping bombs, but not at &quot;after&quot; part, there will be a political price to pay at home.</p>\n<p>There always is.</p>\n<p>Polls may reflect an immediate positive result for Trump, mostly because US lives were not lost, and the operation is considered to be successful.</p>\n<p>But that will change.   Voters in the next few months will not be looking at these actions against Iran as any motivation to vote for Republicans. Not when the SAVE ACT can't be passed, election integrity not solved, and zero arrests for all the assaults on the right, and those involved with Epstein.</p>\n<p>Only a tiny fraction of the base support striking Iran, but they are the loudest.  In fact, if anything, the coalition of voters that Trump assembled to win 2024, from across a wide spectrum, libertarians, cross over Dems etc, will be more divided because of these actions if they do not get wins here at home for American's that are of equal scale or more so, than our giant flexing of military muscle abroad for Israel.</p>\n<p>What comes next for Iran, Trump is leaving to the Iranian's, and that is even more complex a situation than we had to deal with in Iraq.</p>\n<p>You can have your strikes on Iran. But you cannot have no strikes on the deep state, and a Republican congress that cannot codify anything to benefit Americans, and say you are winning anything at this point.</p>\n<p>Maybe i'm wrong, but history proves how these things play out.</p>\n", "score_down": 1, "author_flair_text": "", "p